summary: Y’know I see a lot of people saying how Captain Marvel not smiling that much could be a sign that she’s gonna have a flat...
body: Y’know I see a lot of people saying how Captain Marvel not smiling that much could be a sign that she’s gonna have a flat personality. Now I can see where they’re coming from cause this has happened before (I.e every character in The Last Airbender lmao) but personally, I don’t see it that way. Now I could be proven wrong & her personality could be flat as fuck, but I think they’re going to give her the Levi treatment. Maybe they’re going to give her a flat face, but make it so when something tragic happens she seems just saddened enough that she doesn’t have to cry for us to know how she’s feeling. I’m a total slut for media that does that. Or they could make it so that as the movie progresses & her journey becomes more & more challenging, we see her slowly break down as the movie progresses while still trying to keep an intimidating presence only for the main villain to make her completely break down near the climax, but bring herself back up for the final battle. I have a lot of faith in Marvel cause their main characters are always enjoyable at the very least. They know how to handle their protagonists so I’m not that worried.
